Comments (non-blocking but important):
1) RH usability with current mock context: default `MOCK_SERVIDOR` is non-RH/non-admin, so `/rh/*` always redirects away in normal runtime. Access-control behavior is correct, but there is no built-in role toggle/login mock to exercise RH screens without code edits. This is a testability gap.
2) Minor requirement fidelity gap: Férias “histórico de períodos (gozado/programado/vendido)” is represented as solicitation history/timeline rather than an explicit periods table. Functionally close, but not exact to spec wording.

Security:
- None observed at serious level in this frontend diff. (Client-side role checks exist; no obvious injection/secret exposure issues introduced.)

